<subSubSection id="C3213488FF81CC4339E32ACBFC37BC96" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B846703FF81CC4339E32ACBFC37BC96" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,1689]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis id="B94FBB11FF81CC4339E32ACBFEF3BCB2" bold="true" box="[199,328,1447,1473]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Etymology</emphasis>
. This species is named in honor of Dr. Douglas Zeppelini Filho, Professor at the Universidade Estadual da 
<collectingRegion id="49FFA9E1FF81CC4338202AA7FEE0BC96" box="[260,347,1483,1509]" country="Brazil" name="Paraiba" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Paraíba</collectingRegion>
, who provided us with this material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1C80FF81CC433A2B2AA7FC3CBC96" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1823" box="[783,903,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Apioninae">Apioninae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3213488FF81CC4339E32A82FB42BFEA" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B846703FF81CC4339E32A82FB42BFEA" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,1689]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis id="B94FBB11FF81CC4339E32A82FE9ABF7B" bold="true" box="[199,289,1518,1544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Biology</emphasis>
. Larvae and pupae of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1C80FF81CC433B032A83FC9CBF7A" authorityName="De Sousa &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" box="[551,807,1519,1545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Pygidiapion" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zeppelinii">
<emphasis id="B94FBB11FF81CC433B032A83FC9CBF7A" box="[551,807,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Pygidiapion zeppelinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
develop in floral buds of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1C80FF81CC433D722A83FA27BF7A" authority="Vogel" authorityName="Vogel" authorityYear="1837" box="[1110,1436,1519,1545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Pterocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="violaceus">
<emphasis id="B94FBB11FF81CC433D722A83FAE9BF7A" box="[1110,1362,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Pterocarpus violaceus</emphasis>
Vogel
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1C80FF81CC4339BB297FFEB0BF5D" box="[159,267,1555,1582]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
) (regional name aldrago or pau-vidro), an ornamental tree that occurs from southern 
<collectingRegion id="49FFA9E1FF81CC433DFF297FFAA7BF5E" box="[1243,1308,1555,1581]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Bahia</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49FFA9E1FF81CC433C72297FFF5BBF22" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion id="49FFA9E1FF81CC433823295BFEEDBF22" box="[263,342,1591,1617]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Paraná</collectingRegion>
, on slopes in the Atlantic Rainforest. The tree flowers from October through December, and the fruits and seeds mature in May through July. The plants multiply rapidly and are an indispensable component in reforestation of degraded permanent preservation areas (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1AF2FF81CC433A2A2913FC12BFEA" author="Lorenzi, H." box="[782,937,1663,1689]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" refId="ref7682" refString="Lorenzi, H. (1992) Arvores brasileiras: manual de identificacao e cultivo de plantas arboreas nativas do Brasil. Plantarum, Nova Odessa, 168 pp." type="book" year="1992">Lorenzi 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1AF2FF81CC433A912913FB56BFEA" author="Nakamura, A. T. &amp; Oliveira, D. M. T." box="[949,1261,1662,1689]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" pagination="375 - 387" refId="ref7927" refString="Nakamura, A. T. &amp; Oliveira, D. M. T. (2005) Morfoanatomia e ontogenese da samara de Pterocarpus violaceus Vogel (Fabaceae: Faboideae). Revista Brasileira de Botanica 28 (2), 375 - 387. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0100 - 84042005000200016" type="journal article" year="2005">Nakamura &amp; Oliveira 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
